[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man appears in Cardiff court accused of murder in Ely

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court charged with murdering a father-of-five in Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stephen Pike, 58, is accused of stabbing Clint Simms, 39, to death in Ely, on 3 March.
Mr Pike, of Ely, appeared at Cardiff Magistrates' Court on Monday charged with  murder and possession of a bladed article in a public place.
He spoke only to confirm his name and was remanded in custody to appear at Cardiff Crown Court on Tuesday.
